Issue Identification:
- Determine MFA method in use (authenticator app, SMS, hardware token)
- Identify the system or application affected
- Check if user has access to registered MFA device
- Verify user identity through alternate means

{% if issue_type == 'authenticator_app' %}
Authenticator App Issues:
- Verify time sync on user's mobile device
- Check if correct account is selected in app
- Confirm app has latest updates
- Re-register authenticator app if codes not working
- Provide backup codes if available
{% endif %}

{% if issue_type == 'new_device' %}
New Device Registration:
- Verify user identity using existing MFA or manager approval
- Remove old device registration if applicable
- Guide user through new device enrollment
- Test MFA with new device
- Ensure backup methods are configured
{% endif %}

{% if issue_type == 'expired_token' %}
Expired Token/Session:
- Reset MFA registration in admin portal
- Generate new setup QR code
- Guide user through re-enrollment
- Verify successful authentication
{% endif %}

{% if issue_type == 'sso_errors' %}
SSO Authentication Errors:
- Verify SSO configuration for the application
- Check user's account status in identity provider
- Clear browser cache and cookies
- Test with incognito/private browsing
- Verify SAML/OIDC certificate validity
- Check for identity provider service issues
{% endif %}

Temporary Access (if needed):
- Issue temporary access code per policy
- Set short expiration time
- Document temporary bypass with justification
- Ensure MFA is fully restored before closing

Account Recovery:
- Reset MFA methods if all access lost
- Require strong identity verification
- Notify user of all registered MFA methods
- Recommend setting up backup authentication methods

Resolution:
- Confirm user can authenticate successfully
- Document the issue and resolution
- Update user's security contact information if changed
- Remind user of MFA best practices
